<title type="html"><![CDATA[10/7(Thu.)Miss Korea's victory has been controversial due to her weight./ Table topics session.(Host：William)]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewtopic.php?t=547&amp;p=570#p570"><![CDATA[
10/7(Thu.)Miss Korea's victory has been controversial due to her weight.// Table topics session.(Host：William)<br /><br /><span style="color: #FF0000">Place:</span>Zoom Meeting<br /><span style="color: #FF0000">Agenda:</span><br />07:00-7:05 pm Opening Remarks<br />07:05-7:40 pm Session 1 Group Discussion<br />07:40-8:00 pm Presentation (At least two members of each table are invited, 2 mins / each member)<br />8:00-8:05 pm Break<br />8:05-8:40 pm Session 2 discussion<br />8:40-9:00 pm Presentation<br /><br />Let's join the Zoom meeting this Thursday at 07:00 pm<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://zoomtw.zoom.us/j/92987266213?pw">https://zoomtw.zoom.us/j/92987266213?pw</a><!-- m --> ... 09#success<br /><br /><span style="color: #FF0000">會議 ID:</span>929 8726 6213<br /><span style="color: #FF0000">密碼:</span>112233<br /><br /><br />Session 1<br /><a href="https://youtu.be/ygVxTTKWvdA" class="postlink">https://youtu.be/ygVxTTKWvdA</a><br /><a href="https://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kim_Soo-min_(beauty_pageant_winner)" class="postlink">https://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kim_Soo-min_(beauty_pageant_winner)</a><br />Miss Korea's victory has been controversial due to her weight.<br />Miss Korea 2018 Soo Min Kim received hate from netizens after she was crowned the 62nd winner of the South Korea national pageant.<br />She's 174 cm and 58 kgs.<br />She said any woman, regardless of their height, is overweight when she goes over 50 kgs in Korea.<br />1. What are your thoughts on Miss Korea being called &quot;Too Fat &quot; ?<br />2. Why do some South Koreans think it's normal to tell people they're overweight ? <br />3. Have you ever analyze when ones tell another one that he/she is overweight and should go on diet ? <br />4. Why fat shaming is so common in <br />South Korea ? <br />5. If fat shaming is so ineffective , how come it seems to work well in countries like Japan, Taiwan and South Korea ? <br /><br />Second session is Table Topic.<br />Each of the participants prepare some questions. <br />In the first round the first person ask the question and any participants can answer it. Every participant have the chance to raise the question and answer the participant's question later.<br />In the second round I would like to invite the volunteer to ask  or answer the question. If there is no volunteer I will assign the speaker.<br />---------------------------------------------------------------------<br />P.S.<br />1.因疫情關係，聚會方式改為線上遠距。<br />2.參加三次後，只要繳交1,000元(學生500元)，即可成為ROYAL終身會員!<br />3.請帶著開放與熱情來參加自由的全英文會話聚會~<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=12531">Danny Lin</a> — Thu Sep 30, 2021 10:50 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
